<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   A: Resist Gear is worn during raids or encounters where the mob uses an AoE (Area of Effect) spell that does considerable damage.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Examples of such encounters that you may participate in when you're younger are Vox and Nagafen. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Q: Okay, so what kind of Resist Gear is there? And where can I get it?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   A: Resist Gear is pretty plentiful for many of your various slots.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> The most popular item has to be the Crown of the Froglok Kings. It sells for about 1.5k to 3k and boosts your Fire and Cold resists a whopping +20. It also has 12AC on it and only weighs 0.5, making it one of the most common head pieces for monks.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>List of Easily Gotten Resist Gear -</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Crown of the Froglok Kings -</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Head: AC12 +20 Cold/Fire - Lower Guk<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Runed Bone Fork -</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Ranged: +10 Fire/Cold/Magic - Upper Guk<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Velium Diamond Rings -</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Fingers: +8 All Resists - Crafted<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Golden Diamond Mask -</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Face: +10 Fire/Cold +5 Disease/Poison +3 Magic - Crafted<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Velium Blue Diamond Bracelet -</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Wrist: +9 Fire/Disease/Magic/Poison +11 Cold - Crafted<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Blue Diamond Electrum Earring -</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Ear: +6 Fire/Cold +11 Disease/Poison +4 Magic - Crafted<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Chetari Bonecrafted Shield -</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Back: AC19 +10 Fire - Dragon Necropolis<br>
<br>
The most popular items are the Bone Fork and Crown, they can both be easily gotten and come from the same general area (upper and lower guk respectfully). They can be easily purchased as well. Most 56+ Warriors will have a full set of the above mentioned items. <p>-Zarcath<p><p>

