<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: What is this Coldain Ring I keep hearing about?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
A: It is an involved quest similar to the caster shawl. As you complete stages of the quest, the ring is upgraded by one point on each of its stats; eg, lvl 1 ring is (1 ac 1str 1sv magic), lvl 2 is (2 ac 2str 2 sv magic). At lvl 8 it gains a right-clicky insta-cast damage shield which will stack with all other spells except for the ranger Call of Earth line of spells. At level 9 it gains 9 sta and 50 raw HPs. Finally at lvl 10 the complete stats are (10 ac 10 str 10 sta 100 hp, right-click insta-cast 10pt damage shield).<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: The 9th ring doesn't have a 9-point damage shield?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
A: Nope.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: This ring looks awesome, why do I never/almost never see it?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
A: It is extremely tedious, and a lot of it is hit-or-miss luck. The first ring you have to collect two of the very rare HQ Tundra Kodiak Pelts, which can take anywhere from 30 minutes to months. Finding Rodrick and the invasion plans are a tedious wait as well. The dwarf for the second quest is simply annoying and gets in more trouble than Kragstomper. Depending on server dynamics, people may be in competition for Garadain Glacierbane to do the 8th quest. The 9th quest requires some tedious camps, as well as a high level brewer (of which there are few). The 10th ring is not doable by a run-of-the-mill guild either.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: This sounds altogether too much like the Ragefire camp.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
A: More boring, because guildies are not so concerned with a nice ring for their warr as right-clicky rez, and not so likely to spend hours camping it all with you. However, you won't have to worry so much about KSing. On the other hand, Ragefire has a set spawn time. Completion of the ring quest is unpredictable.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: If I fail the 8th quest, I'll lose all my work?! Help!</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
A: All you need is a healer, some way to go invis, someone with harmony, and preferably either a high level or FDer to single pull just to be safe. Hand in the items to Garadain to start up the event. Be sure and warn the zone so then the people at Ry'gorr fort can clear out. Have your group set up camp inside the fort away from but in sight of the fort entrance. When the named NPCs spawn, harmony, pull the Chief, loot his head. Go invis, and go outside and find Garadain. Wait for him to shout charge, otherwise the event will be broken. When he shouts, turn it all in and receive your new ring! During this time your group is finishing off the named for some nice drops, and the dwarves easily slaughter the giants and orcs.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Q: Is there a walkthrough I can find somewhere?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
A: Yes, but I've told you how to get through the truly risky part. The rest is up to you. <p>~<b><a href="http://www2.kalenda.com/andrew/nobbynob.html">Nobbynob Littlun</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uarrowablaze.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arrow Ablaze</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/21/02 9:57:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2403.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.anyfun.net/animation/gifs/cartoon3.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Common Equipment Questions. READ FIRST before posting.</span><hr size=1> Thanks a lot for all the input, and i'm adding the answered here for the people in the future.<br>
